"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439675","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-06","<p>Unmanned vehicles already play an important role in UK Armed Forces' operations across all environments. On the basis of the Government's National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review of November 2015, the Department is continuing to examine where unmanned systems may offer advantages over manned alternatives and to invest in new unmanned capabilities. For example, the Department is more than doubling the number of armed remotely piloted aircraft available to the UK Armed Forces under the Protector programme to replace the existing Reaper aircraft, and is also developing high-end technologies - including in collaboration with France and the US - under a future Unmanned Combat Air System programme.</p><p>Throughout the Department's development and integration of unmanned systems, the policy is that a human must always be responsible for any decisions on targeting.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-01-06T16:20:48.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439675/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439675/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-21","Military Intervention","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to integrate the use in military operations of unmanned vehicles in the air, at sea, and on land.","false","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL4751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439676","Home Office","false","2016-01-11","<p>HM Government’s Counter Extremism Strategy and counter-terrorism strategy, CONTEST, set out our approach to tackling the full range of factors that allow extremist and terrorist groups to grow and flourish. These include directly challenging ideologies, including those which have a theological basis. The review into funding of extremism in the UK will include funding that comes from overseas.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL4753","2016-01-11T15:05:00.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439676/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439676/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-12-21","Islam","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 17 December (HL4279), whether they plan to collect information about overseas funding of the preaching and teaching of Wahhabism in mosques and Muslim education bodies.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL4752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439677","Home Office","false","2016-01-11","<p>HM Government’s Counter Extremism Strategy and counter-terrorism strategy, CONTEST, set out our approach to tackling the full range of factors that allow extremist and terrorist groups to grow and flourish. These include directly challenging ideologies, including those which have a theological basis. The review into funding of extremism in the UK will include funding that comes from overseas.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL4752","2016-01-11T15:05:00.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439677/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439677/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-12-21","Islam","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of any correlation between Wahhabism and extremism and terrorism in the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL4753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439678","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-01-04","<p>Until Flood Re becomes operational, the insurance industry is continuing to make insurance available to those policy holders at high flood risk, as agreed to in the Statement of Principles.</p><br /><p>Flood Re has submitted a comprehensive application for authorisation to the financial regulators, and is engaging with them. Flood Re is continuing to build and implement the systems necessary to support the operational launch of the scheme in April 2016.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-01-04T14:36:38.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439678/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439678/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-21","Floods: Insurance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the impact of the delay in the introduction of Flood Re on those houses recently flooded in Cumbria and elsewhere.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering",,"Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","HL4754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439679","Home Office","false","2016-01-06","<p>The table below shows the number of interviews conducted in each calendar year since 2007. The lower figures for 2007 reflect the pilot and roll out of the new interview process for all first-time passport applicants and the figures for 2015 are up to week ending 20 December.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year <br></p></td><td><p>Number of Interviews</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>18,160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>293,337</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>261,593</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>296,434</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>269,587</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>273,680</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>283,284</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>253,156</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>221,759</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord Bates",,"2016-01-06T15:44:39.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439679/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439679/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-12-21","Passports: Interviews","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bates on 8 December (HL4116), how many personal interviews with adults applying for a passport for the first time were conducted in each calendar year from 2007 to 2015 inclusive.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL4755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439680","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-05","<p>The defence capability employed to protect the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers will be dependent on a variety of factors such as, but not limited to, the specific task, whether it is a national or coalition commitment, threat levels and theatre of operations.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-01-05T17:02:32.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439680/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439680/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-21","Aircraft Carriers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 18 December (HL4511), whether the Queen Elizabeth class will always deploy with its fully integrated defence capability.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL4756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439681","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-05","<p>The Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers will be protected by a layered defence, the composition of which will be tailored to the threat faced. This defence may include, but not be limited to, submarines and ships within the Maritime Task Group (including their embarked Lightning II aircraft, helicopters and unmanned air systems) as well as land-based aircraft, where applicable.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-01-05T17:02:49.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439681/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439681/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-21","Aircraft Carriers: Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 18 December (HL4510), whether the Sea Lightnings carried aboard the Queen Elizabeth class will be a fully integrated part of the carrier battle group defence capability, as well as its long-range strike force.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL4757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439682","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-08","<p>This information was made available as part of the evidence provided by the Government to the House of Lords Select Committee on the Inquiries Act 2005:</p><p>http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201314/ldselect/ldinquiries/143/14318.htm</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-01-08T14:51:31.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439682/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439682/answer","HL4758 Table of inquiries under other Acts and non-statutory inquiries as at 03... (1).doc","HL4758 Table of inquiries under other Acts and non-statutory inquiries as at 03... (1).doc","Table of Inquiries under other Acts","Table of Inquiries under other Acts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439682/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-12-21","Public Inquiries","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which public inquiries they set up between May 1997 and January 2004; and what was the purpose of each.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL4758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439683","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-08","<p>The information in relation to this time period is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost. However, the total cost on completion of those inquiries which span this time period is available as part of the evidence provided by the Government to the House of Lords Select Committee on the Inquiries Act 2005:</p><p>http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201314/ldselect/ldinquiries/143/14318.htm</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-01-08T14:41:04.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439683/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439683/answer","HL4759 Table of inquiries under other Acts and non-statutory inquiries as at 03... (1).doc","HL4759 Table of inquiries under other Acts and non-statutory inquiries as at 03... (1).doc","Table of Inquiries under other Acts","Table of Inquiries under other Acts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439683/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-12-21","Public Inquiries","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the financial year 2003–04, what was the total cost of each public inquiry conducted; and what was paid to each inquiry chairman, including expenses and VAT.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL4759"
