"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439447","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-01-05","<p>As was stated in the Answer to questions HL2604 and 19495, 3.5 full time equivalent staff (FTE) worked under the Just Solutions International (JSi) brand. These staff also worked on other, core business within the National Offender Management Service (NOMS). As none of these staff were members of the Senior Civil Service, it would not be appropriate to name them in a Parliamentary answer.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-01-05T11:19:44.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439447/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439447/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-17","Just Solutions International: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 17 December 2015 to Question 19495, what the (a) names, (b) job titles and (c) salary bands were of the staff who worked on Just Solutions International.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","20629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439448","Department of Health","false","2016-01-05","<p>The Department is leading the consultation on Fixed Recoverable Costs for low-value clinical negligence claims and there will be a full public consultation, which will be open to all interested parties to make representations.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-01-05T10:19:03.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439448/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439448/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-17","NHS: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to consult the Justice Select Committee on introducing a new streamlined claims process for low cost medical negligence claims.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","20595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439449","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-01-05","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-01-05T12:07:33.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439449/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439449/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-12-17","Ministry of Justice: Information Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many press and public relations staff are employed by (a) the National Archives, (b) the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority, (c) HM Courts and Tribunal Service, (d) HM Prison Service, (e) the Legal Aid Agency, (f) the National Offender Management Service, (g) the Office of the Public Guardian, (h) Cafcass, (i) the Criminal Cases Review Commission, (j) the Judicial Appointments Commission, (k) the Legal Services board, (l) the Parole Board, (m) the Youth Justice Board for England and Wales, (n) the Law Commission, (o) HM Inspectorate of prisons, (p) HM Inspectorate of Prisons, (p) HM Inspectorate of Probation, (q) the Legal Ombudsman, (r) the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman, (s) the Victims' Commissioner; how many of those employees are paid more than (i) £50,000 and (ii) £100,000; and what the total expenditure was on press and public relations by each of those orqanisations in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","20619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439450","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-11","<p>The planned target for staff numbers, published in the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency business plan, is no more than 4470 full time equivalent (FTE) staff by 31 March 2016. The DVSA FTE as at 30 November was 4,396.59 with a difference of 73.41 FTE (vacant posts).</p><br /><p>DVSA is aware that the level of change ongoing within the agency may have impacted on staff, their workloads and their relationships with management.</p><br /><p>A) The select use of temporary promotion and contingent labour has mitigated most of the impact on the workload of staff.</p><p>B) While the results of the recent Civil Service staff engagement survey has shown that staff morale is lower than in previous years, this cannot clearly be linked to the level of vacancies. DVSA has been through a period of significant change which Senior Management believe is more likely to have had an impact on morale. A number of initiatives are being put in place to address levels of staff engagement and morale.</p><p>C) The Civil Service staff engagement survey did show that relations between managers and staff at the local level were good. However, staff were less content with managers at senior levels who were more likely to be associated with issues of concern to many staff, such as the merger, restructuring and modernised terms and conditions.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-11T16:22:30.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439450/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439450/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-17","Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many staff vacancies there are at the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency; and what assessment he has made of the effect of the level of those vacancies on (a) staff workloads, (b) staff morale and (c) relations between staff and management.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","20565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439451","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-05","<p>I recognise the international importance of the HS1 network in allowing high-speed rail services from London to reach Europe, whilst noting that no international services currently serve Stratford International station. Eurostar, in which the government recently sold its 40% stake, accesses the HS1 network on an open access basis and is not subject to the terms of a franchise agreement or a contract let by government. Government has no power to direct or specify that Eurostar stops at Stratford International station. A decision made by Eurostar not to serve Stratford International would be as a result of commercial imperatives and priorities, for example, the potential revenue derived from customers using the station or the increased journey time which a further stop would involve. It would not be appropriate for government to interfere with that decision-making process. I have not received any recent representations on this matter from potential or actual train operators; who in any event, should address their questions to HS1 Ltd, as the infrastructure manager, in the first instance; nor have I held any discussions with Eurostar on the matter of services to Stratford.</p><br /><p>Regarding any aspirations of Deutsche Bahn to commence operation of international services from St Pancras International, this is rightly a matter for HS1 Ltd as the infrastructure manager, who I understand have held discussions with a number of potential new entrants, including Deutsche Bahn. It would not be appropriate to comment on any ongoing commercial discussions between those parties.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry","20556 ; 20557 ; 20558","2016-01-05T16:18:11.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439451/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439451/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-17","Stratford Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent representations he has received on international services stopping at Stratford International station; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","20555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439452","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-05","<p>I recognise the international importance of the HS1 network in allowing high-speed rail services from London to reach Europe, whilst noting that no international services currently serve Stratford International station. Eurostar, in which the government recently sold its 40% stake, accesses the HS1 network on an open access basis and is not subject to the terms of a franchise agreement or a contract let by government. Government has no power to direct or specify that Eurostar stops at Stratford International station. A decision made by Eurostar not to serve Stratford International would be as a result of commercial imperatives and priorities, for example, the potential revenue derived from customers using the station or the increased journey time which a further stop would involve. It would not be appropriate for government to interfere with that decision-making process. I have not received any recent representations on this matter from potential or actual train operators; who in any event, should address their questions to HS1 Ltd, as the infrastructure manager, in the first instance; nor have I held any discussions with Eurostar on the matter of services to Stratford.</p><br /><p>Regarding any aspirations of Deutsche Bahn to commence operation of international services from St Pancras International, this is rightly a matter for HS1 Ltd as the infrastructure manager, who I understand have held discussions with a number of potential new entrants, including Deutsche Bahn. It would not be appropriate to comment on any ongoing commercial discussions between those parties.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry","20555 ; 20557 ; 20558","2016-01-05T16:18:11.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439452/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/439452/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-17","Stratford Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with Eurostar on stopping services at Stratford International station.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","20556"
