"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438843","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-12","<p>Information on the value of apprenticeships funding allocation is not broken down by business type. Since May 2010, there have been 504,900 apprenticeship starts in the retail sector subject area.</p><p>In England, the Government provides funding for training where employers hire an apprentice and currently fully funds apprenticeship training for 16 -18 year olds and up to 50% of apprenticeship training for over 19s.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-12T16:06:24.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438843/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438843/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-16","Apprentices: Retail Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the value was of Government subsidies and financial incentives to retail companies to encourage the creation of apprenticeships in the retail sector since 2010.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","20475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438844","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-13","<p>We do not hold this information.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-13T17:39:16.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438844/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438844/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-16","Apprentices: Retail Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether Government subsidies and financial incentives to retail companies to encourage the creation of apprenticeships in the retail sector were given to companies known to use zero-hours or casual contract since 2010.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","20476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438845","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-05","<p>In line with previous answers on this topic, information relating to the proceedings of Cabinet Committees, including when and how often they meet, and which Ministers have attended, is generally not disclosed as to do so could harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-01-05T11:08:48.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438845/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438845/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-12-16","Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the dates were of all meetings between July and November 2015 of the Cabinet Sub-committee on airports.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","20399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438846","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-11","<p>The Government currently has no plans to alter the rates of VAT relating to the tourist industry.</p><br /><p>I refer the Rt Hon gentleman to my comments during the Westminster Hall debate on 17th March 2015.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-11T17:03:34.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438846/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438846/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","VAT: Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will reduce the rate of VAT on tourism.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","20409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438847","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-18","<p>The pricing of insurance products is a commercial matter for individual insurers in which the Government does not seek to intervene. The motor insurance market is intensely competitive and the Government therefore expects that the insurance industry will pass on savings to consumers.</p><br /><p>Some insurers have already committed to pass on all savings to consumers as a result of the proposed changes.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-18T17:05:14.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438847/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438847/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department plans to use any of its statutory regulatory powers to ensure that there is the reduction in the cost of car insurance referred to in paragraph 1.143 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","20373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438848","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>In general, if, at the end of the day of a residential property transaction, a purchaser owns more than one property and has not replaced a main residence, the higher rates will apply. Where there is a temporary overlap between replacing and selling a main residence, the higher rates will apply but the purchaser will be entitled to a refund of the higher amounts on disposal of the previous main residence within 18 months.</p><br /><p>The Government is consulting on the policy detail, including on the treatment of difficult cases.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-05T12:13:30.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438848/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438848/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Stamp Duty Land Tax: Second Homes","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans that the three per cent additional stamp duty rate on the purchase of a second home will apply to people in the process of moving house who own two properties for a short period of time.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","20402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438849","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>The pricing of insurance products is a commercial matter for individual insurers in which the Government does not seek to intervene. The motor insurance market is intensely competitive and the Government therefore expects that the insurance industry will pass on savings to consumers.</p><br /><p>Some insurers have already committed to pass on all savings to consumers as a result of the proposed changes.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-05T15:21:05.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438849/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438849/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, by what mechanism any savings made by insurance companies as a result of a change to the small claims limit for soft tissue road traffic accident injuries will be passed on to policyholders.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","20350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438850","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<br /><p>The government has taken action on household debt by establishing the independent Financial Policy Committee (FPC) within the Bank of England to ensure emerging risks and vulnerabilities across the financial system as a whole are identified, monitored and effectively addressed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-05T14:06:57.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438850/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438850/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent representations he has received about the level of household debt.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","20351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438851","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>Household debt as a proportion of income has fallen to 144% in Q2 2015, from a peak of 168% in Q1 2008. To avoid repeating the mistakes of the past we have created the independent Financial Policy Committee (FPC) within the Bank of England to ensure emerging risks and vulnerabilities across the financial system as a whole are identified, monitored and effectively addressed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-05T15:23:43.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438851/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438851/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effects on the economy of the level of (a) consumer borrowing and (b) personal loans.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","20352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438852","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>The Ministry of Justice will launch a public consultation in the New Year on the details of the policy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-05T12:43:38.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438852/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438852/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the potential costs and benefits to business of changes to motor insurance proposed in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","20348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438853","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-11","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has a large and long-established presence in Scotland. The Department announced in November its decision to significantly invest in Scotland by creating two Regional Centres in Glasgow and Edinburgh, employing up to 6,300 staff. As part of those transformation plans, HMRC is planning to remain in East Kilbride until 2025-26.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-11T17:00:57.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438853/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438853/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Revenue and Customs: East Kilbride","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of HM Revenue and Customs office closures on the local economy in East Kilbride.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","20362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438854","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-11","<p>The Government is committed to increasing compliance with minimum wage legislation and effective enforcement of it. Everyone who is entitled to the minimum wage should receive it. Employers who pay workers less than the minimum wage not only have to pay back arrears of wages at current minimum wage rates but also face financial penalties of up to £20,000 per underpaid worker. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not keep data in a format to enable provision of the information requested. To reiterate the answer provided to UIN 211605, HMRC will pursue non-payment of arrears through civil recovery action.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-11T17:06:59.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438854/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438854/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 3 November 2014 to Question 211605, how many and what proportion of initial enquiries by HM Revenue and Customs, which sought confirmation that arrears had been paid to workers following enforcement action due to non-payment of the national minimum wage, were unable to confirm that the requisite arrears had been paid in full in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","20432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438855","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>The Government is aware of the reports published by Sir Andrew Large and, separately, by Dr Lawrence Tomlinson into Royal Bank of Scotland (RBS)'s treatment of customers and businesses in financial difficulty.</p><br /><p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) has appointed Promontory Financial Group and Mazars to independently review the allegations in the reports against RBS's practices. If the findings from the review reveal issues which come within the FCA's remit, the FCA will consider further regulatory measures.</p><p>The Government’s shareholding in RBS is managed at arm’s length from HM Treasury by UK Financial Investments (UKFI). However, UKFI’s role is to manage the investment, not the bank. Commercial affairs remain the responsibility of the bank’s independent management team.</p><br /><p>RBS is making progress to deal decisively with the problems of the past, which will allow it to become a simpler, safer and more focused bank that works for the UK economy. Under the leadership of Ross McEwan RBS has made good progress in becoming a simpler, safer and more focused bank that works for the UK economy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","20453","2016-01-05T14:09:28.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438855/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438855/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received about the work of Royal Bank of Scotland's Global Restructuring Group.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","20452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438856","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>The Government is aware of the reports published by Sir Andrew Large and, separately, by Dr Lawrence Tomlinson into Royal Bank of Scotland (RBS)'s treatment of customers and businesses in financial difficulty.</p><br /><p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) has appointed Promontory Financial Group and Mazars to independently review the allegations in the reports against RBS's practices. If the findings from the review reveal issues which come within the FCA's remit, the FCA will consider further regulatory measures.</p><p>The Government’s shareholding in RBS is managed at arm’s length from HM Treasury by UK Financial Investments (UKFI). However, UKFI’s role is to manage the investment, not the bank. Commercial affairs remain the responsibility of the bank’s independent management team.</p><br /><p>RBS is making progress to deal decisively with the problems of the past, which will allow it to become a simpler, safer and more focused bank that works for the UK economy. Under the leadership of Ross McEwan RBS has made good progress in becoming a simpler, safer and more focused bank that works for the UK economy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","20452","2016-01-05T14:09:28.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438856/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438856/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-16","Royal Bank of Scotland and UK Financial Investments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with (a) UK Financial Investments and (b) Royal Bank of Scotland about the effects of decisions by the bank's Global Restructuring Group on (i) small businesses and (ii) the economy of the UK.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","20453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438857","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-05","<p>Reducing tax credits fraud and error is a top priority for HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). The contract with Concentrix offers additional capacity to help build on HMRC’s own work, which has reduced tax credits fraud and error to the lowest ever level. Using a private company provides a cost-effective way to reach additional claims that need checking.</p><br /><p>The checks are to ensure that people are paid the correct amount of money to prevent them from getting into debt which they may find difficult to repay and protect losses to taxpayers.</p><br /><p>Concentrix operate under the same powers and processes as HMRC. Concentrix select cases to be checked using information provided by HMRC. Concentrix decide how best to achieve the expected benefits, including the number and type of cases and number of staff employed. HMRC closely monitors their performance.</p><br /><p>The contract uses a payment by results model, which means Concentrix is only paid based on the money it saves the Exchequer as a result of correcting claims that are incorrect. They will not be paid if the decisions they make about claimants’ awards are incorrect.</p><br /><p>The contract was signed on 6 May 2014. The contract was awarded to Synnex-Concentrix UK Ltd in April 2014, following a procurement exercise advertised under the open procedure. Information about the contract value and contract award is already in the public domain.</p><p><a href="https://www.deltaesourcing.com/delta/viewNotice.html?noticeId=97910033" target="_blank">https://www.deltaesourcing.com/delta/viewNotice.html?noticeId=97910033</a></p><p><br></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","20455 ; 20456 ; 20457 ; 20458","2016-01-05T12:34:04.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438857/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/43885